2.title: The Fear and the Falls
2.plot: The Jackson family doesn't vacation like other people. They need a place where they can be active and continue their training. So this trip, they're headed to Zambia, Africa-home of Victoria Falls, one of the seven wonders of the world, and 25 of the most amazing rapids on the planet.

imdb.plot outline: Series Description: The Jacksons are the "First Family of Kayaking." Father EJ is a four-time world champion. Son Dane might be the best kayaker in the world. And daughter Emily and her husband Nick Troutman are both world champions. Together with EJ's wife Kristine, youngest son KC, and Emily & Nick's toddler Tucker, the family travels the planet in search of insane adventures, world competitions, and the chance to be together. This isn't your typical family. They don't just drive with the top down, they paddle over massive waterfalls, jump off cliffs, and hang out in corners of the world no one ever visits because they are Jackson Wild. Talent Descriptions: EJ Jackson is a 4-time world champion kayaker who has competed for more than 25 years. He has also revolutionized the industry with his Jackson Kayak brand boats. Son Dane is considered by many to be the top whitewater kayaker in the world. He attracts millions of YouTube views every time he goes over a waterfall. He continues to search for higher and faster waterfalls to conquer and races to win. Daughter Emily was a world champion right up until giving birth to her son Tucker. She is making her way back to top and will represent the USA in the World Kayaking Championships. Emily's husband, Nick Troutman, is a Canadian World Champion. He won 23 events in 2014 alone! This year he represents Canada in the World Kayaking Championships. EJ's wife Christine, their youngest son KC, and Emily & Nick's toddler, Tucker, are all along for the ride and adventure.
